  },
  {
    q: "Do you service Lincoln Impinger 1132, Middleby Marshall PS640G, and Bakers Pride VH-1828?",
    a: "Yes. These three platforms cover the LA chain pizza market. Lincoln Impinger 1132 and 1100 series (Welbilt, dominant chain pizza brand including Pizza Hut and Domino's installs), Middleby Marshall PS640G and PS770 (premium chains), Bakers Pride VH-1828 (Standex Food Service conveyor line). We carry common parts on the van.",
  },
  {
    q: "What's air-impingement cooking?",
    a: "Lincoln Impinger pioneered the technology. Hot air is forced through shaped 'fingers' (formed sheet-metal airflow guides) that direct high-velocity heated air onto the pizza top and bottom as it travels on the conveyor. Cooks pizza in 4 to 7 minutes vs 8 to 12 minutes on a deck oven. Different repair playbook from blower-style or radiant-heat conveyor designs.",
  },
  {
    q: "How often does a conveyor oven need service?",
    a: "Chain pizza operations typically see 2 to 3 service calls per year due to high-volume continuous use (12 to 16 hour service days, 7 days a week). Common service items: igniter, thermocouple, conveyor belt cleaning and tension adjustment, blower bearing service, finger inspection. Preventive maintenance contract reduces emergency-call frequency.",
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor warranty. Brand component warranties processed separately through manufacturer service network. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410, BBB A+ accredited.",
  },
];

