<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · What we service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Conveyor pizza ovens for chain operations and high-volume pizzerias.</h2>

    <p>Conveyor pizza ovens move pizza on a wire-mesh conveyor belt through a hot cooking chamber, throughput 60 to 120+ pizzas per hour depending on belt speed and pie size. 30 to 60 inch conveyor lengths. The platform of choice for chain pizza operations (Pizza Hut, Domino's, Papa John's), high-volume independent pizzerias, and stadium concessions.</p>

    <p>Three brands cover the LA chain pizza market: <strong>Lincoln Impinger</strong> (Welbilt brand, the dominant chain pizza oven, 1132 standard, 1100 series mid-size, Express 2501 quick-service variant), <strong>Middleby Marshall</strong> (Middleby Corporation, PS640G and PS770 premium chain platform), <strong>Bakers Pride VH-1828 and VH-1620</strong> (Standex Food Service conveyor line, often in independent operations).</p>

    <p>Lincoln Impinger pioneered <strong>air-impingement cooking technology</strong>, with shaped airflow "fingers" that direct heated air onto the pizza as it travels through the chamber. Different diagnostic playbook from blower-style or radiant-heat conveyor designs. We know the architecture by serial number.</p>

    <p>This is not a deck pizza oven (Bakers Pride Y, Marsal, Cuppone, completely different platform, see <a href="/commercial/pizza-oven-repair/deck-pizza-oven-repair/">deck pizza oven repair</a>) and not a wood-fired oven (Forno Bravo, Wood Stone, refractory dome, see <a href="/commercial/pizza-oven-repair/wood-fired-pizza-oven-repair/">wood-fired pizza oven repair</a>).</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. <strong>BHGS #A49573</strong>. <strong>EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410</strong>. CSLB C-20 HVAC and C-38 Refrigeration scope. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7, no emergency surcharge.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Typical conveyor oven failures</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">High-volume continuous use breaks parts in patterns.</h2>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Conveyor belt motor (year 6 to 9 on chain operations).</strong> Heavy continuous use wears the gearmotor. Per-replacement $720 to $1,100 plus 1.5 to 2 hour labor.</li>
      <li><strong>Conveyor belt itself (wire mesh).</strong> Belt elongates from sustained tension, edges wear, segments deform from heat cycling. Replacement $480 to $780.</li>
      <li><strong>Air-flow finger replacement (Lincoln Impinger specific).</strong> Hot-air "fingers" deform from sustained 600°F+ chamber temp. Lost cooking efficiency, uneven pies. Per-set replacement $1,200 to $1,800.</li>
      <li><strong>Burner blower / impingement air system.</strong> Bearings wear from continuous high-temp operation. $620 to $980.</li>
      <li><strong>Igniter and pilot system.</strong> Heavy cycling on chain operations wears ignition. $260 to $440.</li>
      <li><strong>Thermocouple.</strong> Gas safety, drops millivolt output below valve threshold. $220 to $340.</li>
      <li><strong>Door and window glass.</strong> Thermal stress cracking from open/close cycles plus chamber temp. $340 to $560.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Recent jobs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Real repair stories from the last few weeks.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Composite examples; model numbers, ages, and prices are accurate to typical scope.</p>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>West Hollywood · Lincoln Impinger 1132 chain pizza, 7 years old</h3>
      <p>Pizza chain location. Conveyor stalled mid-shift, 80+ pies queued. Diagnosed: conveyor belt motor seized (year 7 typical for high-volume chain operations). Replaced motor, lubricated drive system, tested 30-minute continuous run. Total: $120 plus $860 motor plus 1.5 hours = $980.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Long Beach · Middleby Marshall PS640G chain location, 8 years old</h3>
      <p>Domino's location. Customer complaints about uneven cooking, undercooked toppings on left side of pies. Diagnosed: air-flow fingers deformed, lost airflow uniformity. Replaced finger set, calibrated air-pressure balance, ran test pies. Total: $120 plus $1,080 fingers plus 2 hours = $1,200.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Pasadena · Bakers Pride VH-1828 independent pizzeria chain, 6 years old</h3>
      <p>Conveyor belt running uneven plus right-side igniter intermittent. Diagnosed: belt elongated past spec tension range, igniter at end of life. Replaced belt with manufacturer-spec wire mesh, replaced igniter. Total: $120 plus $580 parts plus 2 hours = $720.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>San Fernando Valley · Lincoln Impinger Express 2501, 5 years old</h3>
      <p>Pizza Hut location. Cooking chamber temp dropping mid-shift, pizzas slow. Diagnosed: blower bearing wear (year 5 typical on Express variants due to compact design and continuous load) plus thermocouple failing intermittently. Replaced blower assembly, replaced thermocouple. Total: $120 plus $880 parts plus 2 hours = $1,100.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04 · Honest scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we do for conveyor ovens, and what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong> Lincoln Impinger 1132, 1100 series, Express 2501; Middleby Marshall PS640G, PS770; Bakers Pride VH-1828, VH-1620. Conveyor motor and belt, air-flow fingers (Lincoln-specific), burner blower, igniter, thermocouple, door and window glass, control board diagnosis. Both single-deck and stacked double-deck conveyor configurations.</p>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> deck pizza ovens on this page (see <a href="/commercial/pizza-oven-repair/deck-pizza-oven-repair/">deck pizza oven repair</a>); wood-fired ovens (see <a href="/commercial/pizza-oven-repair/wood-fired-pizza-oven-repair/">wood-fired pizza oven repair</a>); new conveyor oven installation (specialty installer trade with gas line plus electrical engineering); chain operation parts logistics where the corporate service network requires specific authorization (we coordinate with corporate-authorized technicians as needed); Type I hood work above the oven (see <a href="/commercial/exhaust-hood-repair/">commercial exhaust hood repair</a>).</p>
  </div>
</section>

